bcl:definition.bcl:text:
auction price means the amount, determined under the auction
procedures, that a successful bidder must pay for the right to apply for a special wine
store licence;

record of unsuccessful bidders means the record of
unsuccessful bidders that the general manager keeps in accordance with section
8;

bcl:paragraph.bcl:text:
the successful bidder has not submitted, within the prescribed time, a complete
          application or fees under the Liquor Control and Licensing Act for a
          special wine store licence for that grocery store;

the successful bidder's application for a special wine store licence for that
          grocery store is refused under the Liquor Control and
              Licensing Act;
